{
  "texts": [
    "Meanwhile, during model training, researchers must make critical decisions about which algorithms to use, how to train them, and how to evaluate their performance (Wang et al., 2022).",
    "In the following sections, we provide an overview of the critical elements of ML-based abstract screening tools-feature extraction methodology, model training, and stopping rule-focusing on ASReview software.",
    "The first major stage in ML-based tools for abstract screening is feature extraction.",
    "Feature extraction is a fundamental process in natural language processing (NLP) that involves transforming raw text data into representative variables that can be used as input for the learning algorithms (Sammons et al., 2016).",
    "Effective feature extraction is essential for ML-based abstract screening tools to capture relevant information that can be used to predict the relevance of an abstract."
  ]
}